    "source_strategy": "BOS + Demand Pullback Strategy",
    "causal_story": "Long-only BTCUSDT 15m baseline that preserves the selected open-source Pine logic: a confirmed pivot high defines structure, a bullish wick BOS plus ATR-sized green impulse creates a demand zone from the most recent bearish candle, and a later pullback/reclaim with a bullish candle pattern and EMA trend filter enters long. This is not the full ASM/Fib/liquidity strategy. It is the baseline parent used to decide whether the open-source BOS-demand engine has enough full-history life before phase-3 ASM mutations are allowed.",
    "future_asm_mutation_queue": [
      "Add short-side symmetry.",
      "Replace EMA100 trend filter with completed 1h structure bias.",
      "Add completed 1h context bars resampled from 15m.",
      "Separate external 15m structure from internal 15m structure.",
      "Require external BOS/CHoCH before active dealing range is created.",
      "Define dealing range from structural origin to impulse extreme.",
      "Add FVG/imbalance requirement inside impulse leg.",
      "Add Fib retracement filter: 67 percent, with 71 and 79 percent alternatives.",
      "Add premium/discount side validation.",
      "Add liquidity sweep before entry: wick through local liquidity, close back inside.",
      "Add internal BOS/CHoCH confirmation after sweep.",
      "Replace fixed 1.5R target with opposing range extreme.",
      "Add range-expiration and invalidation rules.",
      "Test continuation and reversal branches separately."
    ],
    "integrity_notes": [
      "Confirmed pivots must be known only after pivot_len right bars close.",
      "The exact Pine baseline uses wick BOS, not body-close BOS.",
      "The close-BOS and no-EMA variants are diagnostic controls, not phase-3 mutations.",
      "Production-comparable runs use next_bar_open execution instead of same-close fills."
    ]
  },
